This presidential memorandum, issued on January 8, 2021, provides an order of succession within the United States International Development Finance Corporation (DFC). The memorandum states that in the event that the Chief Executive Officer of DFC is unable to perform their duties, the following officers will act as and perform the functions of the CEO in the listed order: Deputy Chief Executive Officer, Chief Operating Officer, Executive Vice President for Strategy, Chief of Staff, Vice President and General Counsel, Deputy General Counsel, Vice President of Structured Finance and Insurance, Vice President of Development Credit, and Chief Financial Officer and Vice President of Finance. The memorandum also includes exceptions and general provisions, stating that individuals serving in an acting capacity cannot act as CEO, and that the President has discretion in designating an acting CEO. The memorandum is to be implemented in accordance with applicable law and subject to the availability of appropriations.